    {
      "title": "Gap metrics not yet on Prometheus",
      "description": "These live in miner-economics/snapshot.py output. Weekly refresh via the Gap C GitHub Action creates issues with these numbers. To surface in Grafana, add a small exporter that reads snapshots.jsonl and publishes gauges.",
      "type": "text",
      "id": 8,
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 24 },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "### Gap-C metrics still on the ground floor\n\n- **Unique external submitters / last 100 tasks** — needs on-chain address cardinality; snapshot.py computes this, not yet exported as a Prometheus gauge.\n- **Fee share of total reward** — computed from measured miner earnings vs count × fee; not in Prometheus.\n- **Approved models in catalog** — exposed via `qfc_getSupportedModels` RPC, not Prometheus.\n- **Daily QFC burn from burned gas** — execution layer may emit this; confirm with core team.\n\n**To add these panels:**\n\n1. Write a `gap-metrics-exporter` (20-line Python) that polls the RPC every 60s and exposes gauges on `:9300/metrics`.\n2. Register it with Prometheus via the existing service discovery.\n3. Return here and add panels:\n   - `gap_b_unique_submitters_last_100` (target: ≥5 at T+4w)\n   - `gap_c_fee_share_ratio` (target: ≥0.40 at T+4w, ≥0.50 at T+12w)\n   - `gap_b_approved_models_count` (target: ≥4 after LLM proposal passes)\n\nUntil that exporter is written, read `miner-economics/snapshots.jsonl` directly or run `python3 miner-economics/snapshot.py`."
      }
    }
  ],
